Base:Descriptions.Base:Description: large brown falcon

A large dark brown falcon with a speckled white and brown chest, lighter colored head with a sharp hooked beak and large black eyes rimmed in yellow. The falcon is about 20 inches long with a wingspan of about 40 inches. Two powerful looking feet are equipped with dangerous talons.
A large dark brown falcon with a speckled white and brown chest, powerful feet and talons, a hooked beak and black eyes rimmed in yellow.
beak
A hooked raptor beak; short but powerful. The tip of the beak is black, shading to a bluish gray at its widest. The cere skin around the beak is yellow in color; two small nostril holes can be seen.
A short, hooked falcon beak
falcon breast
The softly feathered breast of a falcon. The feathers are mostly whitish in color with a pattern of brown speckles and stripes.
The white and brown feathered breast of a falcon.
falcon eye
The large black eye of a falcon, rimmed in yellowish skin. There is a hungry, predatory look in it.
The large black eye of a falcon.
pair of falcon eyes
A pair of large black falcon eyes. They are set so that the bird has binocular vision.
A pair of large black falcon eyes.
feathers
The dark brown and white barred feathers of a falcon.
The dark brown and white feathers of a falcon.
falcon foot
The large taloned foot of a falcon. The foot has four long toes, each with a black curved talon, and is covered in yellowish skin.
The large taloned foot of a falcon.
head

The small head of a falcon covered in light brown and white feathers highlighted with darker edged feathers. Two dark brown streaks run down either side of the beak, highlighting the cheeks. The skin surrounding the eyes and beak is a yellowish color.
The small head of a falcon with big black eyes and a hooked beak.
falcon's upper breast
By observing the falcon's breast carefully you detect it's heart beating rapidly.
The feathered upper breast of a falcon.
leg
The strong leg of a falcon, covered in dark brown and white feathers. The leg has a large, long-toed foot equipped with sharp black talons.
The feathered leg of a falcon, ending in a powerful foot.
neck
The short neck of a falcon with feathers in shades of brown on the back and white speckled with brown on the front.
The short feathered neck of a falcon.
NEW detail
tail
A tail of long dark brown feathers barred with lighter tan and white streaks. It helps the falcon to manuever while flying.
The dark brown feathered tail of a falon.
tail feather
A large dark brown tail feather, barred with stripes of white and tan. It is preened and well-cared for.
A large dark brown and white barred tail feather of this falcon.
talons
A falcon's sharp curved black talons. They can be extended to easily grasp prey.
A falcon's sharp black talons.
wing

A falcon's dark brown feathered wing. Outstretched, this wing appears to be very large and powerful with a pointed shape. The feathers on the underside of the wing are lighter in color, buff tan and white.
The falcon's dark brown feathered wing.
falcon wing feather
The long primary flight feather of a falcon. It is dark brown barred with white and is preened and well cared for.
The long dark brown and white barred wing feather of a falcon.
wings
A falcon's dark brown feathered wings. Outstretched, they appear to be very large and powerful. The feathers on the underside of the wing are lighter in color, buff tan and white.
A pair of dark brown feathered wings.
